\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Scheduled Status Reviews
\series default
:
 The Project Owner shall conduct status reviews at intervals not exceeding twenty-five (25) percent of the chartered project duration,
 measured by elapsed calendar days from project initiation to the chartered target completion date.
 For projects with no defined end date,
 or where the calculated interval would exceed ninety (90) calendar days,
 status reviews shall occur at ninety (90) calendar day intervals instead.
 Each review shall confirm that scope,
 budget,
 and timeline remain on track and shall be documented in the project record.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Any status review that identifies scope expansion beyond the approved charter,
 budget variance exceeding five (5) percent of the approved charter amount,
 or resource reassignment shall escalate to IT Director re-authorization regardless of where it falls on the annual re-authorization clock.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Clarification
\series default
:
 The budget variance trigger applies only where a project budget is formally defined in the charter.
 For external projects with sponsor-owned funding,
 the charter shall state whether the Department controls a defined budget component subject to this threshold.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\series bold
\lang english
Annual Re-Authorization
\series default
:
 For projects exceeding twelve (12) months in duration,
 the IT Director shall provide annual re-authorization confirming that the project continues under its current charter.
 Re-authorization shall be documented in the project record.
\end_layout

