\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.7 Phase 5 —
 Post-Mortem
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Project Owner shall conduct a post-mortem for every formally designated project upon master work order closure.
 Post-mortem timing is tiered by project complexity:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Routine projects
\series default
 —
 those completing within ninety (90) calendar days with no Significant or Emergency changes —
 shall complete the post-mortem within fourteen (14) calendar days of master work order closure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Complex projects
\series default
 —
 those exceeding ninety (90) calendar days in duration,
 involving Significant or Emergency changes,
 or involving vendor delivery —
 shall initiate the post-mortem upon Assistant IT Director confirmation of go-live stability,
 with a hard outer bound of thirty (30) calendar days from master work order closure regardless of stability status.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Project Owner shall ensure the post-mortem addresses:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Whether the project achieved its defined success criteria.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Scope,
 budget,
 and timeline variance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Risks that materialized and the means by which they were resolved.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Stakeholder and communication plan effectiveness.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Actionable takeaways for future projects.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The post-mortem summary shall be documented in the project record and retained with the master work order.
 Stakeholders designated in the project charter shall participate in the post-mortem review as specified in the charter.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Project Owner shall document training requirements identified during a project in the project charter and shall communicate them to the relevant department for that department's own planning purposes.
 End-user training delivery carries no project closure gate obligation under this policy.
\end_layout

